-- CFM confirms trials of new jet engine, says schedule intact
-- By Tim Hepher
-- Thu Oct 09, 2014 06:36AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, Oct 9 (Reuters) - CFM International, a joint venture between General Electric <GE.N> and France's Safran <SAF.PA>, confirmed on Thursday it had started flight trials of its next-generation LEAP engine and said it was "on track" to win safety certification in 2015.

Reuters reported earlier that a version of the engine being developed for Chinese planemaker Comac had begun flight trials earlier this week [ID:nL6N0S41K7].